OL,3,CThe #13 bn hole in the government's
OL,4,C2.6% defence target
OL,6,FBen Wallace, the former defence
OL,7,Fsecretary, tells me this is absurdly
OL,8,Fhigh. But I am trying to give the
OL,9,FTreasury the benefit of the doubt.
OL,11,FEven with my generosity there is a #12
OL,12,Fbillion gap. And by the way, even if
OL,13,Fevery single penny of intelligence
OL,14,Fspending was attributed to defence,
OL,15,Fthere would be a #7 billion gap!
OL,17,FOne Treasury official said another
OL,18,F#1.6 billion is probably the #1.6
OL,19,Fbillion annual cash cost of army
OL,20,Fpensions.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
