OL,3,CThe #13 bn hole in the government's
OL,4,C2.6% defence target
OL,6,FNone of what I've just said takes away
OL,7,Ffrom the published fact that defence
OL,8,Fspending is rising 3.8% faster than
OL,9,Finflation for the next three years.
OL,11,FThat is a huge amount of resource
OL,12,Fbeing transferred to defence.
OL,14,FBut if when you read that the UK is
OL,15,Fset to spend 2.6% of GDP on defence,
OL,16,Fyou thought all of that significant
OL,17,Fexpenditure was on the armed forces,
OL,18,Fmunitions, military satellites, nukes,
OL,19,Fplanes and boats - as I did - you need
OL,20,Fto think again.
